* Iris watched as Quake continued to stay on duty, noting his intent to make 
sure that there wasn't an enemy alive that would get past him.
She would have smiled if she would have had any lips, or a face for that 
matter.
However, her voice sounded just as happy as any of her expression would have 
ever been.*

" Intent little soldier, aren't we?"

* Her voice echoed through the empty hollow of the Ark, though, luckily it 
was only heard there and not through the whole thing.
However, her scanners also detected another being that just happened to be 
near the Ark, scanning the new being as well and diesovering it to be a 
large cat. ( SnowCat )
She looked over the feline with her scanners and saw that she seemed a 
little down, wondering just what was making this bot so down.*

" Troubles?"

* Her voice now soft and soothing as her voice directed itself towards 
SnowCat, not being able to be heard my Quake.
It was amazing what a comp program could do...when it wasn't just a 
program.*
